                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-27T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 27, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 28—5:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>382. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 26, 3 p.m. Yesterday’s Japanese press reports that at a cabinet
                            meeting at Changchun on March 24th it was decided (1) to retain for the
                            present the existing customs system of the Chinese Republic together
                            with the existing tariffs; (2) to remit monthly to the Inspector
                            General, Shanghai, the portion of the customs receipts required for
                            service of the foreign loans; and (3) to retain the surplus for the use
                            of new government.</p>
                        <pb facs="0740" n="636" xml:id="pg_636"/>
                        <p>It appears that except for the retention of the surplus revenue the
                            existing customs administration will not be interfered with for the
                            present.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
